<HEAD>Late Porn Star Confessed To Role In Slayings, Ex-Wife Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Pornographic film star <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Holmes </PERSON> tearfully confessed to a role in the bludgeoning deaths of four people, charges he was acquitted of in 1982, his ex-wife said. <PERSON> Holmes </PERSON>, who died last month of complications stemming from AIDS, told his ex-wife, <PERSON> Sharon </PERSON> <PERSON> Holmes </PERSON>, that he led three killers to a hillside home and stood by while they murdered four people, the <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> reported in Thursday's editions. Ms. <PERSON> Holmes </PERSON>, who divorced the actor in 1984, said in a recent interview with the newspaper that <PERSON> Holmes </PERSON> confessed his role to her shortly after the slayings in July 1981. However, he said he did n't participate in the murders and never told her the names of the killers, she said. Another woman who had a longtime intimate relationship with <PERSON> Holmes </PERSON> and asked not to be identified said he made a similar admission to her, the newspaper said. She reported that admission to police in 1981. Together, the women's stories corroborate the <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>'s theory of how the killings happened. <PERSON> Holmes </PERSON>, who died March 13 at age 43, was tried and acquitted in a 1982 trial. No one but <PERSON> Holmes </PERSON> has ever been charged in the murder of <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Launius </PERSON>, 37; <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> DeVerell </PERSON>, 42; <PERSON> Joy </PERSON> <PERSON> Audrey </PERSON> <PERSON> Miller </PERSON>, 46; and <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON>, 22. The actor appeared in hundreds of sexually explicit films in the 1970s and early'80s, when he was the porn industry's leading male star.
