 Torrejon </LOCATION>. There have been many demonstrations in recent years at <LOCATION> Torrejon </LOCATION> protesting <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military bases in <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION>'s membership in the <ORGANIZATION> North </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Atlantic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Treaty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>. In January, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> agreed to withdraw within three years a tactical wing of 72 F-16 fighter bombers from <LOCATION> Torrejon </LOCATION>. That was part of a new eight-year pact on <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> military units in <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION> that will replace a five-year accord which expires May 14. The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> armed services maintain three air bases and a naval station in <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION> that involve some 10,000 military personnel. President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> ordered the air raids on <LOCATION> Libya </LOCATION> in retaliation for alleged <LOCATION> Libyan </LOCATION> links to the bombing of a nightclub in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> that killed two <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> servicemen and a Turkish woman.
