ces. He said he also looked for progress with <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> over higher quotas for <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> beef and citrus products. Otherwise, <PERSON> Yeutter </PERSON> said, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> will press its complaints before <ORGANIZATION> GATT </ORGANIZATION>.
