 Unexpected news of an increase in the nation's trade deficit sparked a major slide in the stock market Thursday, with the <ORGANIZATION> Dow </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jones </ORGANIZATION> industrial average tumbling 101.46 to 2,005.64. The dollar and bond prices also dropped in response to the report. The dollar fell to 123.73 Japanese yen from 126.44 yen; the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION>'s bellwether 30-year issue fell $ 10 per $ 1,000 in face value while its yield rose to 8.86 percent from 8.73 percent late Wednesday. Oil prices jumped to new highs, while gold also moved higher.
