<HEAD>Oil Futures Prices Close Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Oil prices are benefiting from the stock market drop and from rumors about the scope of <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION>'s planned meeting with non-cartel exporters, market watchers say. On the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the May-delivery price for <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intermediate </ORGANIZATION> crude closed up 18 cents per barrel to $ 18.30 on Thursday. It was the highest since a Dec. 11 close at $ 18.31. Refined products traded on the exchange were mixed. Heating oil rose 0.49 cent per gallon to 49.51 cents, and unleaded gasoline fell .06 cent a gallon to 52.36 cents. `` We had a strong day here today, but it was nervous throughout,'' said <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Beutel </PERSON>, assistant director of <ORGANIZATION> Elders </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, an energy futures trading concern in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. Traders said some buying in the oil market came from investors who dumped stocks and were seeking havens for their money. The stock market tumbled after the <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> reported a widening trade deficit in February. Others said the market was driven partly by rumors that the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exporting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Countries </ORGANIZATION> was expanding its list of non-cartel guests at a previously announced meeting on April 23. News of <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION>'s plans to enlist outside support for boosting oil prices has been the key reason for a market rally over the past few days.
