Americas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Cain </PERSON> now has seven plants on the Gulf Coast of <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> and is the nation's fifth-largest maker of ethylene, a component of PVC plastic The merger will make <ORGANIZATION> Occidental </ORGANIZATION> the country's third-largest ethylene producer. <ORGANIZATION> Occidental </ORGANIZATION> Chairman and Chief Executive Officer <PERSON> Armand </PERSON> <PERSON> Hammer </PERSON> credited <PERSON> Cain </PERSON> with having built `` a strong position in petrochemicals with its large, cost efficient ethylene plants and its top quality high density polyethlyene facilities and products.'' He said he expects the acquisition to `` significantly improve <ORGANIZATION> Occidental </ORGANIZATION>'s net income and cash flow'' in the long term. The acquisition, which is expected to be completed in early May, will bring <ORGANIZATION> Occidental </ORGANIZATION>'s long-term debt to $ 6.34 billion, a spokesman said. <ORGANIZATION> Occidental </ORGANIZATION> is involved in businesses including oil, gas, chemicals, fertilizers, coal and meat products.
