<HEAD>Kodak Furloughs Employees in Panama</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Eastman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> has given its workforce in <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> a 15-day paid furlough because of the extreme difficulty in doing business there, a company spokesman said today. The catalyst for the shutdown of <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION>'s marketing facility, retail film and camera shops and mini-lab processing centers was last Friday's economic sanctions imposed by President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>, said <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Kaska </PERSON>. `` We were n't ordered to close, but it just does n't make sense to stay open,'' <PERSON> Kaska </PERSON> said. `` We are not permitted to pay our utility bill. We ca n't pay the phone bill. We were also concerned about the security of our people traveling in that country.'' The sanctions were ordered April 8 by <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> in an effort to force military leader <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> to surrender his hold on the Central American country. They include prohibiting payments to the <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> regime by all <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> citizens and organizations in <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>, freezing the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> assets of the Panamanian government, and prohibiting any person or company in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> from making any payments to the regime. <PERSON> Kaska </PERSON> said he did n't have an exact figure on the number of <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION> employees, but estimated it was less than 1,000. He said the furlough went into effect Tuesday. `` After the 15 days we'll reevaluate and reassess and determine whether there should be another furlough,'' <PERSON> Kaska </PERSON> said. `` We hope the situation will stabilize within a month.'' He said <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION> would continue to service its copiers in the <ORGANIZATION> Panama </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Canal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Zone </ORGANIZATION> and will keep its photo processing mini-labs open there.
