<HEAD>Dollar Retreats Further on New Economic Data, Gold Prices Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The dollar finished lower against major foreign currencies on Friday after another disappointing set of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> economic indicators, but dealers said central bank intervention tempered its fall. The pound rose strongly as investors again moved in to take advantage of higher British interest rates. Gold prices moved up around the globe. The dollar was hurt by news that <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> producer prices increased a larger-than-expected 0.6 percent during March and that industrial output climbed 0.1 percent, less than expected, during the month. However, any further fall in the dollar was tempered by reported intervention from the <ORGANIZATION> Deutsche </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bundesbank </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> and the Bank of <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>. `` The dealers did n't wish to take on the central banks,'' one trader said. In <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, where the business day ends as <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>'s begins, the dollar fell 2.02 yen to a closing 124.13. Later, in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, it was quoted at 123.90 yen. In <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, it cost $ 1.8890 to buy one pound, dearer than $ 1.8755 Thursday. Other late dollar rates in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, compared with late Thursday's rates, included: 1.6605 West German marks, down from 1.6635; 1.3720 Swiss francs, down from 1.3745; 5.6325 French francs, down from 5.6390; 1.8630 Dutch guilders, down from 1.8680; 1,232.50 Italian lire, down from 1,244.00; and 1.2335 Canadian dollars, down from 1.2368 Gold rose in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> to a late bid price of $ 456.25 a troy ounce, compared with late Thursday's $ 451. In <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>, gold was higher, closing at a bid $ 455.50, compared with $ 450.50 late Thursday. Earlier, in <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>, gold rose $ 5.45 to close at a bid $ 454.93. Silver bullion prices rose on the <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> market where the metal was trading at a late bid price of $ 6.49 a troy ounce, compared with Thursday's $ 6.43.
