<HEAD>Comsat Revenues Up Sharply</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Satellite </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> on Friday reported a 68 percent jump in its first quarter profit over a year ago. Net income for the three months ended March 31 totaled $ 14.3 million, or 77 cents a share, compared with earnings of $ 8.5 million, or 44 cents, in 1987. Revenue totaled $ 84.1 million vs. $ 80.7 million. Operating income, however, fell from $ 22.9 million to $ 18.4 million, the company said. The jump in revenue was attributed largely to the acquisition of full ownership in <ORGANIZATION> Comsat </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Video </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enterprises </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which was added to the company in the second quarter of last year. This was partially offset, though, by a decline in revenue from <ORGANIZATION> Intelsat </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Satellite </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>. While international business was up, revenue declined because of rate reductions to customers under long-term contracts, <ORGANIZATION> Comsat </ORGANIZATION> reported. <ORGANIZATION> Comsat </ORGANIZATION> provides international, domestic and maritime communications facilities via satellite and researches communications techniques.
