 <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> T </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Olson </PERSON> will not attend the company's annual meeting Wednesday in <LOCATION> Denver </LOCATION> because he is not healthy enough after undergoing surgery last month for colon cancer, the company said Friday. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Allen </PERSON>, president and chief operating officer of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telephone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Telegraph </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, will preside over the meeting instead, the company said. <PERSON> Olson </PERSON>, 62, is recuperating at home after surgery March 25 and is receiving outpatient chemotherapy, the company confirmed earlier this week. `` It's too early to say when he'll be back,'' <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON>, a company spokesman, said Friday.
