<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0222</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oil Futures Prices Rise Again</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Oil prices continued to advance Friday in light trading, reaching the highest levels since December. On the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the May-delivery price for <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intermediate </ORGANIZATION> crude, which closed up 18 cents per barrel Thursday, rose another 7 cents to $ 18.37. It was the highest since a Dec. 11 close of $ 18.31 per 42-gallon barrel. Among refined products traded on the exchange, wholesale heating oil rose .24 cent a gallon to 49.75 cents after a 0.49 cent rise Thursday, and wholesale unleaded gasoline rose 0.25 cent a gallon to 52.61 cents after falling .06 cent Thursday. Traders said Friday's gains were based largely on internal market influences rather than any outside news. `` What you have today is more of an absence of sellers rather than any aggressive buying,'' said <PERSON> Jayne </PERSON> <PERSON> Ball </PERSON>, a trader in the energy futures department at <ORGANIZATION> Dean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Witter </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reynolds </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. Prices have advanced recently in response to plans for a meeting of oil producers from inside and outside the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exporting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Countries </ORGANIZATION> on April 23. Gains also had been spurred Thursday by investors who dumped stocks as the market tumbled in response to the <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>'s disappointing report on <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> trade.
